Text.SourceString: A new farmer in town?//You moved here <Italic>after</> the oil spill? Huh.//<portrait=normal>I’m <NPCName>Zarah</>. //See you around.
I was sailing the other day, and you wouldn’t believe how much trash I saw at sea.//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm…
It’s upsetting to see nature being covered in trash like that.
Going on an adventure, <PlayerName>$player</>?
How was your weekend?//I had a good one, thanks for asking.
I woke up unmotivated this morning. It’s one of those days, I guess.
Going on an adventure, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I kind of like it here on Coral Island.//<portrait=happy>Who knows? Maybe someday I’ll buy a house and move to a place that doesn’t rock…//<portrait=thinking>Sounds dull, to be honest.
Oh, you’re the chatty type.//<portrait=normal>Don’t be insulted if I don’t say hi to you first, okay?//Probably I either don’t see you, or I’m too distracted to notice anything.
If you’re looking for tips, I know a thing or two about combat.//<portrait=normal>For instance, you don’t want to go into combat without armor…//Common sense, yeah?
Camping in a cavern for more than two days is a nasty business. I don’t miss it.//<portrait=annoyed>How can a place be damp and hot at the same time?
I kind of like it here on Coral Island.//<portrait=happy>Who knows? Maybe someday I’ll buy a house and move to a place that doesn’t rock…//<portrait=thinking>Sounds dull, to be honest.
Oh, you’re the chatty type.//<portrait=normal>Don’t be insulted if I don’t say hi to you first, okay?//Probably I either don’t see you, or I’m too distracted to notice anything.
There are ancient scrolls scattered around the island… It’s true.//<portrait=normal>But there’s no way of knowing exactly where they are.//So we just have to explore lots of different places.
I found some scrolls when I was fishing the other day. Fishing!//<portrait=surprised02>Who would’ve thought?
I kind of like it here on Coral Island.//<portrait=happy>Who knows? Maybe someday I’ll buy a house and move to a place that doesn’t rock…//<portrait=thinking>Sounds dull, to be honest.
I kind of like it here on Coral Island.//<portrait=happy>Who knows? Maybe someday I’ll buy a house and move to a place that doesn’t rock…//<portrait=thinking>Sounds dull, to be honest.
Life feels bland when I’m not after something…//<portrait=annoyed>Pity, really.
It makes me feel stuck, you know?//<portrait=thinking>Like I’m in a cycle of endless adventures… One after another.//<portrait=happy>Now, is that a good thing or a bad thing? I’ll let you decide.
My thoughts? There may be more to this island than meets the eye.
Do you think it’s up to us to find out?//Or is it our duty to wait until nature is ready to show us?
You know, here’s an idea. It might not be a bad thing if I started gardening.//<portrait=normal>After all, I eat a lot of veggies.
Maybe… Maybe after the town fixes the community garden, I’ll try my hand at growing something.
Pro tip, <PlayerName>$player</>. Always carry a weapon in your bag.//Just in case you encounter nasty bugs.
My thoughts? There may be more to this island than meets the eye.
Do you think it’s up to us to uncover these hidden mysteries?//Or should we wait until nature is ready to open up?
I kind of like it here on Coral Island.//<portrait=happy>Who knows? Maybe someday I’ll buy a house and move to a place that doesn’t rock…//<portrait=thinking>Sounds dull, to be honest.
I spent practically the whole day yesterday looking for fresh vegetables, and I still came up short.
Maybe the lake is a better spot for foraging… Hmm…
I should start leaving my boots by the door.//I bring so much mud into the boat.
Ah, I don’t know. Doesn’t sound very convenient.
I get why some people like to work alone…//<portrait=concerned>It’s nice to have an extra hand, but coordinating can be a pain.
I’d rather work alone too…//On my own schedule and by my own rules.
I’m thinking of putting a big, fun bell on the bow of my boat.//<portrait=happy>Like a doorbell for a house.
That way, no one will ever sneak up on me unawares!//Could be fun, I think…
Cooked plenty of food yesterday.//I don’t think I’ll need to make any more until tomorrow.//But I am craving some grilled fish.
Maybe… Maybe I can grill just one fish for today. That way I’ll still have to eat up my other food tomorrow.
The island is full of mystery. I’ve been saying that for years! Glad to see someone else thinks so.
Exhibit A: Just this morning, I found a fresh loaf of bread outside my boat. I wonder who left it there.
I feel like we’re in this big game of life, and we’re fated to go on endless adventures.
Wow! That would be the dream!
I’ve done a lot of camping, and I’ve had my fair share of roasted chestnuts.//It’s safe to say I’m a bit sick of them now. Yuck.
If it weren’t for the chatter around town, you’d never know <NPCName>Jim</> is a very skillful fisher.//He doesn’t fish much anymore and doesn’t really talk about it.
I see myself in <NPCName>Jim</> a lot. At times it makes me wonder if I’ll ever stop looking for new adventures and finally find satisfaction in life.
I used to have a bad allergy to cats.//<portrait=normal>But thankfully, I outgrew it.
I can play with cats now, but I still sneeze here and there… It’s not bad at all, though.
Visitors? No. People don’t visit me…which is cool because I like my space.
Don’t worry about it! I’m sure it’s because I’m away a lot. I rarely spend much time on the boat.
This morning, I found a fresh loaf of bread outside my boat.//I wonder who left it there.
A raccoon, you say? Not convinced. A raccoon would’ve eaten it, I’d think.
You know about the treasure chests on this island, right? There are plenty of them in the sea or buried in the cavern.//If you break them open, there may be valuable things in them.
A little tip from one treasure hunter to another.
Those cats… Er…Bread and Butter? Did I get the names right?//They’re pretty smart.
Yeah! Peanut and Butter, right… <NPCName>Erika’s</>, right? Yeah. Them.//I see them walking around town at night sometimes.
I feel like we’re in this big game of life, and we’re fated to go on endless adventures.
Wow! That would be the dream!
I used to have a bad allergy to cats.//<portrait=normal>But thankfully, I outgrew it.
I can play with cats now, but I still sneeze here and there… It’s not bad at all, though.
I’ve done a lot of camping, and I’ve had my fair share of roasted chestnuts.//It’s safe to say I’m a bit sick of them now. Yuck.
Those cats… Er…Bread and Butter? Did I get the names right?//They’re pretty smart.
Yeah! Peanut and Butter, right… <NPCName>Erika’s</>, right? Yeah. Them.//I see them walking around town at night sometimes.
You know about the treasure chests on this island, right?//There are plenty of them in the sea or buried in the cavern. If you break them open, there may be valuable things in them.
A little tip from one treasure hunter to another.
I once got into trouble with a client because he wanted his money back. The problem was the government took the treasure I found, and my client sued me for unfinished work.
It was a mess. My hands were tied, and I couldn’t do anything about it. Good thing it’s all behind me.
Now that Spring is here, I’m ready to search for treasure again.
I’d have to say Spring and Fall are the best seasons to hunt for treasure. It isn’t too hot, and there’s enough daylight.
I can’t wait for the Cherry Blossom Festival. There’s going to be a lot of good food.//And people. Not a bad thing, actually.
I’m impatient for Spring to get here. I have so many leads for where to find treasure. Maybe even too many.
Are you ready for the start of a new year, <PlayerName>$player</>? I know I’m raring to go.
The mud can be annoying in Spring, but it’s still better than the cold Winter for treasure hunting.
What are you bringing for the hot pot, <PlayerName>$player</>? I think I’ll bring whatever fish I manage to catch… Or cookies.
It’s nice that the sun is up longer, but… Never mind.

You never realize how important daylight is until you find yourself scrounging around the woods in the dark, looking for valuables, and end up bringing home a bunch of useless things.//Trash, pretty much… Yeah.
I spend a lot of time at the beach in Summer.//Anyway, why wouldn’t I?
I understand the Beach Cleanup Festival is really important, but do they have to do it all day?
It’s pretty much Fall, and… Wait, no it isn’t.//<portrait=thinking>It’s only the second week of Summer… I thought it was the 20th already.

The forest is my preferred hangout spot… Not that I don’t like the sea.//<portrait=happy>There’s plenty of food growing around, especially this time of year. You get hungry? You can easily forage and light up a fire.
I’ve been catching a lot of groupers lately.//They’re…<Italic>not</> pretty. But all fish taste pretty much the same after you grill them.

I’m not saying you can only eat grilled fish in Fall. Grilled fish is top-tier food that can be enjoyed any time of day, any time of year.//<portrait=happy>But it’s so much better when the weather’s a bit frisky. Like in Fall.

Do you ever find random crabs on your farm?//<portrait=thinking>The rice field <Italic>right</> behind your farm is full of them… This time of year, anyway.//<portrait=normal>Pretty much all I caught the last time I fished there.
What am I grilling tonight?//<portrait=thinking>Hmm… I’m thinking monkfish. I have some in the fridge.//<portrait=normal>Caught plenty from the dock yesterday.

The forest is my preferred hangout spot… Not that I don’t like the sea.//<portrait=happy>There’s plenty of food growing around, especially this time of year. You get hungry? You can easily forage and light up a fire.
There are a lot of delicious things to forage this time of year, and I really appreciate it. There’s no need for me to go shopping most days.
I’m looking forward to <NPCName>Betty’s</> mooncakes. It’s a shame she doesn’t make them more often.
I’ve been having grilled fish almost every meal for the past two weeks. I think I may have a problem.
Daylight is getting shorter and shorter. Looks like I’ll have to stop my exploration pretty soon.
You seem pretty much as active in Winter as you are in Summer.//<portrait=happy>Not that I’m keeping tabs… We just seem to travel a lot of the same paths… Well, this year, anyway.
Since I can’t spend a lot of time out there, I usually read up on the treasures I’m looking for.//The history, clues to their locations, things like that.
Have you tried tilling the soil on your farm? You might find some stuff…//<portrait=thinking>Oh, but it’s pretty much ice right now, huh?

Fished a little the other day and caught a green sawfish.//<portrait=normal>Have you tried catching them? You should, since they only come out in wintertime. I caught it right outside your farm… You know where that giant tree is? It was in the body of water across from the hot-air balloon area.//I’d try in the evening. I think they hide during the day.

A client once wanted me to search for a chalice in the dead of Winter.//<portrait=annoyed>I said no way, unless he was willing to pay me ten times my usual rate.//<portrait=happy>He gladly waited until Spring.
It’s not just the cold that makes treasure hunting a pain in Winter. Soil is much harder to dig too… Pretty much concrete at this point.//Better to just wait until the ice melts.
The boat isn’t really the best place to live in Winter. There’s a lot of wind, and it’s really hard to keep the heat going.

Have you ever fished near the mayor’s house in Winter?//I heard from the young fisher you can catch silver arowana there.//<portrait=thinking>Long black hair? Yeah, that’s the one.//<portrait=happy>Oh, the one with bright-red boots, not the one with glasses. She’s not a fisher, I don’t think.//<portrait=thinking>But I don’t really know… Never see her around much.
It’s going to be one hot Summer, isn’t it?//I can already tell.
I went on an adventure to discover a buried temple one time and filled my bag with weapons and no food.//<portrait=normal>I thought there’d be food for me wherever I went. Being not picky and all.
I could <Italic>not</> have been more wrong. There was hardly any food, and I ran out of energy in the middle of a battle.//<portrait=annoyed>I passed out and was found by a local blacksmith.
Don’t make the same mistake I did, <PlayerName>$player</>…//Pack some food.
You’re not the only new person here.//Have you met <NPCName>Surya</>?
He moved here just before you did.//<portrait=normal>Heard it was for coral reef restoration. He’s some sort of doctor, I believe. Not the medical kind.
Have you met <NPCName>Scott</>?//I see him at the cavern every now and then.

I’ve been collecting clues about this island’s secrets.//Though I put my mission off for the Winter and decided to enjoy the weather instead. I can’t wait to get going again.//<portrait=happy>Now that it’s Spring, I’ll continue my adventure.
The question is, will I find anything new today?
You look all sweaty. Long day at the farm?
I learn something new every day on this island if I look closely enough.
The heat is exhausting.
But there are plenty of wild vegetables growing.//That’s a good thing for someone like me, who relies on nature a lot for food.
You know, here’s a thought. It may not be a bad idea for me to start gardening.//<portrait=normal>After all, I eat a lot of veggies.
Maybe… Maybe after the town fixes the community garden, I’ll try my hand at growing something.
I heard you worked in a big city before becoming a farmer.
Oh, that’s right! I heard about that.
That makes sense. I can tell from your outfit. It’s very…um…artistic.
Ah, I see.

Special.SourceString: Yes. I ran a small company from my apartment.

Text.SourceString: Of course studying counts! Good luck with that. I believe we never really stop learning.

Special.SourceString: Does studying count? I was a student. In a way, still am.

Text.SourceString: Ah! What’s that like? I feel like we’re all in a big simulation game sometimes.

Special.SourceString: I made games. It’s really fun, but it’s not as easy as I thought it was going to be.

Text.SourceString: All righty, then. Good day to you.

Special.SourceString: I’d prefer to keep that to myself.

Text.SourceString: I hate roasted nuts. Nuts are easy to find and simple to roast, but they taste like rotten charcoal.
I gathered several coconuts around the inn the other day, and I haven’t touched them.//<portrait=thinking>What should I make with them? Hmm…
The only thing I know how to make with coconut milk is lodeh.//<portrait=normal>But I’m not in the mood for it. Hmm…
You can tell it’s Fall from all these chestnuts. They’re everywhere, like weeds!
If you haven’t noticed, the ruins and temples tell stories. They’re about the island’s history and folklore.
Oh! Do you feel that wind?
It’s hard to get any warm sunlight lately. It’s making me feel a bit down.
I have a love-hate relationship with cold weather. It makes me feel like I have endless energy.//<portrait=annoyed>But at the same time, it’s harder to find wild vegetables.
If you haven’t noticed, the ruins and temples tell stories.//They’re about the island’s history and folklore.
There are ancient scrolls scattered around the island. But there’s no way of knowing exactly where they are.//So we just have to explore lots of different places.
I found some scrolls when I was fishing the other day. Fishing!//<portrait=surprised02>Who would’ve thought?
I’m making small changes on the boat.//<portrait=normal>I think it’s a bit tidier.
Oh! Do you feel that?
The wind is getting strong.
You’re always welcome here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
The weather couldn’t be better for reading… Or swimming.//<portrait=surprised>Or heck, fishing!
I caught some fish a little while ago.//<portrait=thinking>I think I’ll make soup with them for dinner.
Well, I personally prefer grilled fish to fish soup.//But today, it just feels like soup kind of weather.
I caught some fish a little while ago.//<portrait=thinking>I think I’ll make soup with them for dinner.
Well, I personally prefer grilled fish to fish soup.//But today, it just feels like soup kind of weather.
The weather couldn’t be better for reading… Or swimming.//<portrait=surprised>Or heck, fishing!
There are fish that come out only in the rain.//So look out for those.
I might as well make my day productive and fish for a bit. Right?
I want to keep close to my boat on rainy days like this.//<portrait=annoyed>Just in case the rain gets really strong, and my boat gets swept away.
Ha ha! Is that weird?
Join me fishing, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I think I’ll head inside in a little bit and make myself a warm meal.
Oh! Do you feel that?
The wind is getting intense.
You’re always welcome here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
The weather couldn’t be better for reading… Or swimming.//<portrait=surprised>Or heck, fishing!
I caught some fish a little while ago.//<portrait=thinking>I think I’ll make soup with them for dinner.
Well, I personally prefer grilled fish to fish soup.//But today, it just feels like soup kind of weather.
There are fish that come out only in the rain.//So look out for those.
I might as well make my day productive and fish for a bit. Right?
I want to keep close to my boat on rainy days like this.//<portrait=annoyed>Just in case the rain gets really strong, and my boat gets swept away.
Ha ha! Is that weird?
I think I’ll head inside in a little bit and make myself a warm meal.
Oh! Do you feel that?
Well, I personally prefer grilled fish to fish soup.//But today, it just feels like soup kind of weather.
The weather couldn’t be better for reading… Or swimming.//<portrait=surprised>Or heck, fishing!
Thankfully, I have a small heater on my boat for snowy days like this.
It’s too cold for me to sail.
I caught some giant stingrays earlier.//It really has been a productive day for me.
I think I’m going to read a bit and call it a day.
You have a lot of snow on you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
The weather couldn’t be better for reading.
Why do I always see you here?
You live near here, right?
Right over there?
Oh, listen, listen. I tried docking my boat right by your farm, but it got too quiet at night.//<portrait=happy>So I bailed. Doesn’t bother you, huh?
You aren’t lost, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>? You look like a mess alone in the middle of the forest.
Living at the pier is great because it’s close to the store and close to people.//It’s nice to know they’re right there.
I like being able to hear people chatting.//<portrait=concerned>It makes it feel less lonely on the boat.
There’s something about this forest that feels mysterious to me.
I have to say, I do like my space.//I mostly keep busy on the island, so it doesn’t leave me much time to socialize.
I learned these ruins have been here since the first human settlement.
Why do you think they built this?
Not now, <PlayerName>$player</>.
But maybe we can chat again sometime?//<portrait=annoyed>Now just isn’t a good time.
It’s a nice surprise to see someone familiar here.
At first, I thought you were…//<portrait=surprised>A bear or something.
Should I move my boat here?
The water is calmer where I am, though.
The weather is great for a beach day today.
I think it’s good for me to come here once in a while.//Besides, spending too much time on a small boat can get claustrophobic.
I’m supposed to go to the forest today, yet here we are.
What am I doing here? That’s a good question.
Taking a break from farming?
I’m always on the lookout for a new adventure.//Look closer, <PlayerName>$player</>. This town is full of it.
I guess you could say I live in town.//Sure doesn’t feel like it sometimes.
It’s really nice to see you here!
Not that many people come to this side of town.//<portrait=happy>Most people like to visit the park instead.
I didn’t hear you knock. Umm…
What can I do for you?
I bought this boat with the payment I got for helping a rich family retrieve a lost heirloom.
I’ve basically lived here ever since.//<portrait=happy>Comfy, isn’t it?
Do you think you could ever live on a boat?
It is fun! But I wouldn’t recommend it if you get seasick easily.
That’s cool too.

Special.SourceString: No, I prefer a home on solid ground.

Text.SourceString: No reason.//Living on a boat can be fun, but I wouldn’t recommend it if you get seasick easily.
Don’t mind the mess. I need to keep things where they are, or I wouldn’t be able to find my stuff.
Watch your step, please.//<portrait=normal>I don’t want you to accidentally step on my things.
For my last job, I lived outdoors almost a whole year.
That was when <NPCName>Walter</> hired me to find his family’s lost heirloom.//<portrait=happy>I spent the year camping around the island to look for it… So much fun!
It’s very nice of you to visit!
I never get to know a lot of people very well…//I don’t really mind it, though, because I tend to move around a lot anyway…//That said, I’m glad I’ve stayed long enough to get to know you.
You’re a good friend, <PlayerName>$player</>.
On land, the breeze feels different from the way it does on the ocean. At sea, it feels…endless.
If you find anything on the island that looks really old, take it to the museum! It might be a rare artifact.
I get a lot of questions about what I do. I’m an adventurer, plain and simple.
Maybe being an adventurer isn’t the most conventional career out there.//I get why people are confused. Heh heh.//Is it even considered a career path, you think? Hmm…
You look tired, <PlayerName>$player</>. Don’t feel down – it’s only Tuesday!//<portrait=normal>There’s so much more time for adventures this week.
I wonder what civilizations were here before us.//What was happening hundreds of years ago on this very spot?
Life moves more slowly out here. It’s nice not to have to stick to a work schedule, isn’t it?//Just how I like it.
On the other hand, a schedule gives you structure.//I guess there are good things and bad things about it.
What sort of adventures have you had on your farm? I’d love to hear about them sometime!
Living on a boat can be hard. Nature can turn on you in an instant… Be prepared, <PlayerName>$player</>.

I found a beautiful vintage-looking cut gem on the beach the other day… Must be at least 100 years old.//I don’t think it belongs to anyone, so I’m going to add it to my collection. It’ll be a centerpiece!
Some kids on the island asked me if I’d ever use my boat for racing. I had a good laugh at that.
I told them maybe. It’s probably better for living in than racing.
I wonder what civilizations were here before us.//What was happening hundreds of years ago on this very spot?
<Italic>Achoo!</>
Excuse me! I’m so sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>.//My nose is acting up.
There’s tons of fish around here, you know. I see them under the surface all the time.
I wonder if there are shipwrecks down there… I bet there’s treasure!
People always tell me my gem collection is worth a lot of money, but I would never sell any of my stones.
I don’t care what they’re worth.//They remind me of adventures I’ve been on.
I keep hearing stories about legendary treasures scattered all over the island.//It’s my job to investigate!
Sometimes people ask if my boat has a name.//I’ve never really thought about it.
I’ve always just thought of it as “mine.”
Today’s the day I usually clean out the boat. I should probably jump in and do that, shouldn’t I?
I should have started earlier, but I had more exciting things to do.//Wouldn’t you rather hunt for buried treasure than clean?
What are you up to today, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I hope you’re taking a little time to explore.
A life in Pokyo… Interesting! We gotta swap stories sometimes. You look like you have cool ones to share.
Not today…ha ha. Thanks, though!
I think a cat somehow got into my lunch yesterday.//I ate my sandwich and sneezed a little.//Weird.
Some people say you can see strange things if you look closely at precious gems. I don’t think they can tell the future or anything like that, but they’re very pretty.
I don’t have a lot of time to read, but I like to pick up a history book now and again.
Did you know Coral Island’s ecosystem has changed a lot in the past several hundred years?//<portrait=normal>There are a lot of old fossils around here that tell the story. It’s so interesting!
Sometimes people bring me gems and ask me to identify them.//I don’t know most of them, though. <NPCName>Rafael</> can tell you about all that. I just appreciate their beauty.
<NPCName>Sam</> offered me some leftover roasted nuts the other day. It was nice of him, but I turned them down.//<portrait=annoyed>Eating nuts is like chewing on wood.
What do you like to do on your days off? I used to go on adventures in my spare time.//Now I get to do it all the time!
Ha! That’s okay. I wouldn’t say I’m a hermit.//<portrait=happy>It’s more like knowing who I am, what I like and dislike, and sticking with it.

What’s the biggest treasure you’ve ever found? I found this stone tablet last year that ended up going to a museum.//It’s halfway across the world now. The plaque underneath it has my name on it and everything.
When you live on a boat, you get to know all the ocean’s emotions.//Calm, upset, furious… It really is just like a human being.
Even though the air is warmer now, the ocean is still very cold. I wouldn’t want to dive off the deck of my boat quite yet.
I don’t know too much about farming, but I do know Spring is when you’re supposed to plant flowers.
I don’t think I need flowers on my boat.//My gem collection is colorful enough.
Coral Island is always beautiful this time of year.//<portrait=normal>It’s beautiful year-round, but it really blooms in the Spring.
The Summer haze makes adventuring much more enjoyable. Everything feels heavy, still, and mysterious.
Do you think we’ll get any storms soon, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’d rather know ahead of time if they’re coming.
If a storm’s coming, I have to prep my boat… It’s a long process.
Having a Summer birthday isn’t too bad. It means I get extra hours of daylight to celebrate.
Not that I do much celebrating, though.//That’s not really my style.
Feel that chill in the air? Winter’s on its way, <PlayerName>$player</>.
I feel closest to nature in Fall. The beautiful colors, piles of leaves on the ground… It’s something to be thankful for.
Grilled fish are delicious this time of year. I catch them from my boat and cook them myself.
It’s a good, warm meal for cold nights.
All this snow on the ground means buried treasure is harder to find. It’s no fun to dig through wet snow, either.
The ocean may rage with storms in Summer, but it can be just as bad in Winter.//And it’s a lot colder.
As much as I love my boat, I feel a little trapped during Winter.//I don’t want to stay inside, but I don’t want to go out into the cold air, either.
Some people escape to Winter houses in warmer climates when it gets too cold outside.//I suppose I could move my boat somewhere warmer in Winter.
I like Coral Island too much to do that, though. I’ll just make sure to keep the heat on all the time.
Sam’s sells delicious cookies. I can never get enough of them.//Have you tried them?
As an adventurer, I’m okay with getting dirty, grimy, dusty, and everything else…but I still hate getting wet.
I wish I could stick around and talk, but I want to stay as dry as possible.
It’s easy to slip when it’s dark and rainy like this, especially when you’re walking on a wet deck.//Be careful.
Look at it pour out there. Do you think it’ll clear up soon?
I like to think rain is nature’s way of telling us to take a break. It helps plants grow, provides water for animals, and pushes us humans inside.
Even when I’m safely inside for the night, I can still feel the rain hitting the deck and the roll of the waves outside.//At least it’s not too windy.
Going somewhere?
Thankfully, I bought some supplies for the boat the other day.//You know…flour, eggs, cookies…the usual.//<portrait=thinking>It’d be annoying to be outdoors when it storms like this.
Thanks for coming to talk, but I’d rather be alone right now.
I need to make sure, uh, my boat is okay. And that I’m okay too.
I just can’t stay focused on this book.
Maybe I should just go to bed. I’m not going to get anything accomplished while the weather is this bad.
Snow makes me just as soggy as rain does. Like a stale chip…//…Left too long between the couch cushions.
I was supposed to go spelunking today, but I had to postpone it because of this snow. I guess I’ll just stay close to home for now.
